         <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="p:4;100:32">A limitation of the PCI Express architectural model is that it allows only a single root and that the root and all of the EPs must share a common address space. In many applications a need exists to interconnect two independent PCI domains. A Non Transparent Bridge (NTB) enables this inter-domain communication, facilitating communication between devices in different switch partitions. This enables both hosts and EPs to initiate transactions to hosts and/or EPs in another switch partition.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="p:5;103:32">Switchtec implements NTB through the use of virtual EP functions. In the case where a USP is used both to connect devices that are transparent to the host above and to serve as an NT EP to communicate with another host, the Switchtec USP can be configured as a dual-function port with one function serving the job of a standard transparent USP and the other function serving the job of providing the NT EP to communicate with another host/root complex.<ph status="deleted" rev="deltaxml-delete" class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="ph:1;103:527"> EP.</ph>
            <xref href="#xd_02b41e45ebfa9eb5-3bb4aa9a-14b7f6ef931--8000/fig_NTB_Architecture_Block_Diagram_1igy9baqi" class="- topic/xref " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="xref:2;108:39" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 2</xref> illustrates the two modes of operation available in Switchtec. On the left is the dual-function mode while on the right is a single NT EP Only mode of operation.</p>
         <note audience="MSCCInternal" class="- topic/note " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="note:3;113:35">
