            <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="title:3;130:35">NTB Architecture Block Diagram</title>
            <image href="graphics/ntb_architecture.svg" placement="break" width="6in" class="- topic/image " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="image:2;136:36"/>
         </fig>
         <p class="- topic/p " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="p:7;141:32">Each NT EP advertises one or more memory windows using PCI BARs. The firmware allocates PCI memory space to the BAR for the NT EP during enumeration.</p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="ul:1;145:33">
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="li:1;148:29">Management BAR: The Management BAR is used for management purposes.The Host RC configures the NT interconnection through registers exposed in the Management BAR space. Any TLP targeting the Management BAR is routed to the switch FW where the vEP firmware module will dispatch the request to NTB Control Firmware. NTB Control Firmware configures the topology of the NTB interconnection, including mapping the NTB BAR to other partitions. The Management BAR resides in BAR0/1 by default, but can be configured to any of the NT EP BARs.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="li:2;151:29">NT BAR: When the NTB receives a memory operation that targets an NT BAR in NT EP, it translates the address of the transaction to a new address in another PCIe domain and forwards the transaction to that domain. Completions are handled in a similar manner.</li>
         </ul> There are two modes for the NT EP:<ph audience="PMCInternal" class="- topic/ph " status="unchanged" xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\ntb\trident_ntb_ntb_overview.xml" xtrc="ph:2;156:33"> Mode 1 and Mode 2.</ph>
      </section>
